<!--
annotation:
Latin: _l
English: _e
Ambiguous item (numbers, ...): _a
Proper name: _n

orthographic idiosyncasies, not always consistent:
oe = e (proelium = prelium)
ae = e (meae = mee)
t = c (expeditio = expedicio)
u = v (ut = vt), iff classical Latin u occurs as the first letter of a word
v = u (invictus = inuictus), iff classical Latin v occurs inside a word
d = t (sed = set), only applies to this one particular word
ch = c (pulcher = pulcer)
h = ch (nihil = nichil)
-->

